 On the other hand, this function reads and creates all solvers specified
 in the XPL.
 However, in this tutorial, we will create the solver in the Python script.
 In order to do this, continue writing 
\family typewriter
tutorial2.py
\family default
:
\begin_inset listings
inline false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

efm = optical.EffectiveFrequencyCyl("efm")
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

efm.geometry = GEO.main
\end_layout

\end_inset

